        <h1>Antivax founder of major Christian TV network dies of Covid-19</h1>

                <time class="op-published" datetime="2021-12-01T11:57:07+00:00">1 Dec, 2021 11:57</time>
            </header>

    
    
    <p><strong>The prominent televangelist and founder of vaccine-skeptical Daystar Television Network, Marcus Lamb, has died of coronavirus complications.</strong></p>
    <p>His death was announced by the network, which describes itself as one of the two largest Christian television broadcasters in the world, on November 30.</p>
<p>A week before Lamb&rsquo;s death his wife Joni confirmed that he had been hospitalized with Covid pneumonia, with their son Jonathan citing a &ldquo;<em>spiritual attack from the enemy</em>.&rdquo;</p>
<p>&ldquo;<em>As much as my parents have gone on here to kind of inform everyone about everything going on to the pandemic and some of the ways to treat Covid &ndash; there&rsquo;s no doubt that the enemy is not happy about that</em>,&rdquo; Jonathan Lamb said during the broadcast on November 23.</p>
        
